modules.description: This module renders box structures to text with precise control over formatting, including styled output using ANSI codes, string length calculation, and direct terminal or channel output. It supports custom extensions for rendering elements, handles UTF-8 encoded strings for accurate display width, and integrates with OCaml's Format module for pretty-printing. Concrete use cases include generating aligned and styled terminal output, logging structured data to files, and embedding box displays in interactive command-line interfaces.
